Barley is a cultivated grain used as animal fodder, as a source of fermentable material for beer and certain distilled beverages, and as a component of various health foods. It is used in soups and stews, and in barley bread of various cultures. Barley grains are commonly made into malt in a traditional and ancient method of preparation.
A hyssop food product is a product made with the leaves, flowers, or oil extract of the hyssop plant.
A mangosteen food product is a food product made from the mangosteen tree.

A lotus plant food product is a seed, pip, rhizome, leaf or flower product obtained from the lotus plant.

Pinus edulis, the Colorado pinyon, two-needle piñon, pinyon pine, or simply piñon, is a pine in the pinyon pine group whose ancestor was a member of the Madro-Tertiary Geoflora (a group of drought resistant trees) and is native to the United States.

definition.value: Stone pine nut food product is a pine nut product made from the stone pine (Pinus pinea), which has been cultivated for its nuts for over 5,000 years.
A whole raw salmonberry is a berry harvested from the salmonberry plant.

The durian is the fruit of several tree species belonging to the genus Durio. There are 30 recognised Durio species, at least nine of which produce edible fruit, with over 300 named varieties in Indonesia, 100 in Thailand and 100 in Malaysia. Durio zibethinus is the only species available in the international market.
A durian is the fruit of several tree species belonging to the genus Durio.

Perideridia oregana is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common names Oregon yampah and eppaw. It is native to Oregon and California in the western United States, where it grows in woodland and other habitat.
A squashberry is a berry from the squashberry plant.

Malus is a genus of about 30–55 species[3] of small deciduous trees or shrubs in the family Rosaceae, including the domesticated orchard apple (M. pumila syn. M. domestica) – also known as the eating apple, cooking apple, or culinary apple. The other species are commonly known as crabapples, crab apples, crabtrees or wild apples
Catjang (Vigna unguiculata subsp. cylindrica) is a subspecies of cowpea. The catjang plant is native to Africa, and is an erect densely branched shrubby perennial of Old World tropics.

Vaccinium arboreum (sparkleberry or farkleberry) is a species of Vaccinium native to the southeastern and south-central United States, from southern Virginia west to southeastern Nebraska, south to Florida and eastern Texas, and north to Illinois.
